race.comment: Tough way to finish with quite a few winning hopes. The Victorian raider BIG WATCH (5) looks one of the horses to beat. The stable has enjoyed great success campaigning horses in SA in recent times. This horse has been freshened and trialed well for this. He maps to get the perfect run and, if he produces his best figures from Victoria, he will go close. SHADOW EAGLE (10) looks a danger, although he will likely concede a start from the wide barrier. He's placed all three runs at this track and distance and his form this campaign is solid. MESROUR (9) was dynamic last start and he might be able to go on with it now. He's always looked a smart horse and he is capable of winning this. MINTULEE (14) could run along with the claim and take some catching, while FREE BEER (1) always seems to finds himself in the last race and, inevitably, always seems to run well. The punters will cheer if he looms up to them.
